               <p>JOHN FORRESTER. I was in Church-row, Aldgate, met the prisoner, and asked him to walk with me. When we got to the watch-house I asked him to walk in, he refused, and called out Murder! he threw something out of his hand which appeared like silver they fell in the street. The mob picked up seven counterfeit shillings. Some others fell on Mr. Death's leads.</p>
               <p>MR. 
               <persName id="t18180909-129-person1064">
                  THOMAS 
                  EDWARD DEATH
               <interp inst="t18180909-129-person1064" type="surname" value="EDWARD DEATH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180909-129-person1064" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180909-129-person1064" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a linen-draper, and live at Aldgate. I picked up two shillings off my leads, which I marked (looks at them) these are them.</p>
               <p>MR. 
               <persName id="t18180909-129-person1065">
                  CALEB 
                  EDWARD POWELL
               <interp inst="t18180909-129-person1065" type="surname" value="EDWARD POWELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180909-129-person1065" type="given" value="CALEB"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180909-129-person1065" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . They are all counterfeit, and of the same die.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I took three of them of a gentleman for some hare-skins; while I was examining them the officer took me.</p>
